{{Infobox football biography | name = Iiro Aalto | fullname = Iiro Aalto | image = Iiro Aalto.JPG | height = {{Height|m=1.80|precision=0}} | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1977|07|19}} | birth_place = Rauma, Finland | currentclub = | clubnumber = | position = Left Defender | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 2001–2002 | clubs1 = [[FC Haka]] | caps1 = 49 | goals1 = 0 | years2 = 2003–2007 | clubs2 = [[HJK Helsinki]] | caps2 = 112 | goals2 = 1 | years3 = 2007–2008 | clubs3 = [[Olympiakos Nicosia]] | caps3 = 6 | goals3 = 0 | years4 = 2008 | clubs4 = [[Tampere United]] | caps4 = 6 | goals4 = 0 | years5 = 2008–2009 | clubs5 = [[Turun Palloseura]] | caps5 = 31 | goals5 = 0 | years6 = 2010 | clubs6 = [[PoPa (loan)]] | caps6 = 5 | goals6 = 0 | years7 = 2010–2015 | clubs7 = [[Pallo-Iirot]] | caps7 = 130 | goals7 = 12 | nationalyears1 = | nationalteam1 = | nationalcaps1 = | nationalgoals1 = | pcupdate = 14 October 2009 | ntupdate = 14 October 2009 }}
'''Iiro Aalto''' (born 19 July 1977) is a Finnish former [[Association football|football]] player. He started his career with Finnish football club Pallo-Iirot, then moved to [[FC Haka]] and spent most of his career at [[Helsingin Jalkapalloklubi]] but from December 2007 played for Cypriot club [[Olympiakos Nicosia]]. Aalto returned to [[Finland]] in May 2008 to play for Tampere United. After his loan spell at Tampere he moved to [[Turun Palloseura|TPS Turku]].
