{{Infobox journal | title = Life Sciences | cover = [[File:LifeSciencesJournalCover.gif|x200px]] | editor = L.E. Wold | discipline = [[Pharmacology]] | formernames = | abbreviation = Life Sci. | publisher = [[Elsevier]] | country = | frequency = Weekly | history = 1962-present | openaccess = | license = | impact = 2.702 | impact-year = 2014 | website = http://www.journals.elsevier.com/life-sciences/ | link1 = http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/journal/00243205 | link1-name = Online access | link2 = | link2-name = | JSTOR = | OCLC = 01715961 | LCCN = 85644789 | CODEN = LIFSAK | ISSN = 0024-3205 | eISSN = 1879-0631 }} '''''Life Sciences''''' is a weekly [[peer-reviewed]] [[scientific journal]] covering research on the molecular, cellular, and [[physiology|physiological]] mechanisms of [[pharmacotherapy]].
Indexed by [[Web of Science|ISI]] Life Sciences received an [[impact factor]] of 2.702 as reported in the 2014 Journal Citation Reports by Thomson Reuters, ranking it 53rd out of 123 journals in the category "Medicine, research & experimental"<ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2015 |chapter=Journals Ranked by Impact: Medicine, research & experimental |title=2014 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition= Sciences |accessdate= |work=Web of Science |postscript=.}}</ref> and ranking it 103rd out of 254 journals in the category "Pharmacology & Pharmacy".<ref name=WoS1>{{cite book |year=2015 |chapter=Journals Ranked by Impact: Pharmacology & pharmacy |title=2014 Journal Citation Reports |publisher=Thomson Reuters |edition= Sciences |accessdate= |work=Web of Science |postscript=.}}</ref>
The current Editor in Chief is Loren E. Wold.<ref>[http://www.journals.elsevier.com/life-sciences/editorial-board/ Life Science Editorial Board]</ref>
