{{Infobox football biography | name = Patrick Aaltonen | image = | image_size = 200px | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=y|1994|3|18}} | birth_place = [[Raisio]], [[Finland]] | height = {{height|m=1.73}} | position = [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|Defender]] | currentclub = [[PTT Rayong F.C.|PTT Rayong]] | clubnumber = 20 | youthyears1 = 2005–2009 | youthclubs1 = [[Helsingin Jalkapalloklubi|HJK]] | youthyears2 = 2010–2012 | youthclubs2 = [[FC Honka|Honka]] | years1 = 2011–2013 | clubs1 = [[FC Honka]] | caps1 = 19 | goals1 = 0 | years2 = 2011–2013 | clubs2 = → [[Pallohonka]] (loan) | caps2 = 27 | goals2 = 1 | years3 = 2014 | clubs3 = [[HIFK Fotboll]] | caps3 = 24 | goals3 = 0 | years4 = 2015 | clubs4 = [[FC Honka]] | caps4 = 5 | goals4 = 0 | years5 = 2015 | clubs5 = [[Ubon UMT United F.C.|Ubon UMT United]] | caps5 = 15 | goals5 = 3 | years6 = 2016 | clubs6 = → [[Internazionale Pattaya F.C.|Internazionale Pattaya]] (loan) | caps6 = 4 | goals6 = 0 | years7 = 2016–2017 | clubs7 = [[FC Honka]] | caps7 = 2 | goals7 = 0 | years8 = 2017 | clubs8 = [[IF Gnistan]] | caps8 = 20 | goals8 = 0 | years9 = 2018– | clubs9 = [[PTT Rayong F.C.|PTT Rayong]] | caps9 = 3 | goals9 = 0 | nationalyears1 = 2010–2012 | nationalteam1 = [[Finland national under-17 football team|Finland U17]] | nationalcaps1 = 14 | nationalgoals1 = 2 | nationalyears2 = 2014–2015 | nationalteam2 = [[Finland national under-21 football team|Finland U21]] | nationalcaps2 = 5 | nationalgoals2 = 1 | pcupdate = 11:40, 8 December 2017 (UTC) | ntupdate = | medaltemplates = {{medalTeam|[[FC Honka|Honka]]}} {{medalW|[[Finnish Cup]]|[[2012 Finnish Cup|2012]]}} }}
'''Patrick Aaltonen''' ({{lang-th|พาทริค อัลโตเน่น}}, born March 18, 1994), simply known as Pate, is a [[Finnish people|Finnish]]-[[Thai people|Thai]] professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|Defender]] for [[PTT Rayong F.C.|PTT Rayong]].<ref>[http://www.smmsport.com/reader.php?news=152882/เทพอินทรี กระชาก 'พาทริค อาลโตเน่น' เล่นในไทยสมใจอยาก]; smmsport.com June 10, 2015</ref><ref>[http://www.smmsport.com/reader.php?news=153193/พาทริค อาลโตเน่น ผมอยากติดทีมชาติไทย]; smmsport.com June 12, 2015</ref>
==Personal life== Aaltonen was born in [[Raisio]]. His father is [[Finnish people|Finnish]] and his mother is Thai.
==Club career== Patrick Aaltonen began his career in 2011 playing for [[FC Honka]] in Finland. [[Ubon UMT United F.C.|Ubon UMT United]] bought him in 2015. At the 2015 season he played well and the club promoted to the [[Thai Division 1 League]]. Fall 2016 Aaltonen returned to [[FC Honka]] in [[Kakkonen]].
